<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Publish Your OOS</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-8">Capture your AI coordination intelligence in a structured format. Claims with confidence ratings, evidence types, and failure modes.</p>

  <form id="publish-form">
    <!-- Step 1: Template -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-4">1. Choose Your Template</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="agent_army" class="sr-only" checked>
          <div class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">Agent Army</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">For orgs with named AI agents that have defined roles and coordinate with each other.</div>
        </label>
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="value_chain" class="sr-only">
          <div class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">Value Chain</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">For orgs that map AI capabilities to their business process flow.</div>
        </label>
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="org_chart" class="sr-only">
          <div class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">Org Chart</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">For orgs that map AI capabilities to departments and functions.</div>
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2: Generate Your OOS -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
        <h2 class="font-semibold">2. Generate Your OOS</h2>
        <button type="button" onclick="togglePrompt()" class="text-xs text-otp-500 hover:underline" id="prompt-toggle-btn">Show prompt</button>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-4">Copy this prompt, fill in the bracketed sections, and give it to any AI (Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini). Upload the resulting .md file in Step 3.</p>

      <div id="prompt-section" class="hidden">
        <div class="relative">
          <pre id="generation-prompt" class="bg-gray-50 border rounded-lg p-4 text-xs text-gray-700 whitespace-pre-wrap overflow-x-auto max-h-[500px] overflow-y-auto leading-relaxed">I need you to generate an OOS (Organizational Operating System) file for my organization.

Here is what we do: [Describe your business in 2-3 sentences]

Here is our AI setup:
[List your AI agents, automations, or AI-augmented workflows. For each one, describe:
- What it does
- What tools it uses
- What it owns vs. what it does NOT own
- Who/what it reports to or escalates to]

Here are the rules we follow:
[List any rules, policies, or patterns you have about how your AI operates.
Examples: "All emails require human approval before sending",
"The analytics bot reports but never recommends",
"If two agents disagree, the founder decides within 24 hours"]

Here are things that went wrong:
[List 2-5 failures, mistakes, or surprises you discovered while building
your AI setup. Be specific. These are often the most valuable claims.]

Here are the boundaries between AI and human:
[What decisions are human-only? What does AI handle autonomously?
Where is the line?]

Now generate an OOS file in this exact format:

1. YAML frontmatter between --- delimiters with: oos_version "1.0",
   org_pseudonym, industry, org_size (solo/small/medium/large/enterprise),
   template (agent_army/value_chain/org_chart), agent_count, platforms
   used, generated_at (ISO timestamp), version 1, parent_version null,
   word_count, claim_count, confidence_distribution (high/medium/low
   counts), evidence_distribution (counts per evidence type)

2. A Purpose section (2-3 sentences)

3. A Prime Directives section (3-5 top-level rules)

4. At minimum 15 claims using this format:

**[C001]** section_name
- **Rule:** [Clear, specific rule]
- **Why:** [Why this exists]
- **Failure mode:** [What breaks when violated]
- **Confidence:** HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW
- **Evidence:** HUMAN_DEFINED_RULE | OBSERVED_ONCE | OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY
  | MEASURED_RESULT | INFERENCE | SPECULATION
- **Scope:** [Where this applies]

Sections: core_operating_rules, agent_roles_and_authority,
coordination_patterns, operational_heuristics, failure_patterns,
human_ai_boundary_conditions

Rules for claims:
- Every claim must have all 6 fields
- Be specific and concrete, not generic
- Failure modes should describe real consequences
- Include at least 2-3 failure_patterns claims
- Total word count between 1800-3000 words
- Minimum 10 claims, aim for 15-25</pre>
          <button type="button" onclick="copyPrompt()" id="copy-prompt-btn"
            class="absolute top-2 right-2 px-3 py-1.5 bg-white border rounded-md text-xs font-medium text-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-50 hover:text-otp-500 transition-colors shadow-sm">
            Copy
          </button>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-2">After you get the .md file, upload it below. Our auto-fixer will clean up any formatting issues.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3: Content -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
        <h2 class="font-semibold">3. Upload Your OOS</h2>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <button type="button" onclick="downloadTemplate()" class="text-xs text-gray-500 hover:underline">Download Template</button>
          <button type="button" onclick="loadExample()" class="text-xs text-otp-500 hover:underline">Load Example</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Upload zone -->
      <div id="upload-zone"
        class="relative border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-8 text-center cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-400 hover:bg-otp-50/30 transition-all mb-4"
        onclick="document.getElementById('file-input').click()">
        <input type="file" id="file-input" accept=".md,.markdown,.txt" class="hidden">
        <div id="upload-prompt">
          <div class="mx-auto w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-otp-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-otp-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16a4 4 0 01-.88-7.903A5 5 0 1115.9 6L16 6a5 5 0 011 9.9M15 13l-3-3m0 0l-3 3m3-3v12"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Upload your .md file</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Drag and drop or click to browse. Accepts .md, .markdown, .txt</p>
        </div>
        <div id="upload-success" class="hidden">
          <div class="mx-auto w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-green-50 flex items-center justify-center mb-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1" id="upload-filename"></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400" id="upload-meta"></p>
          <button type="button" onclick="clearUpload(event)" class="mt-2 text-xs text-red-500 hover:underline">Remove and start over</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pre-validation checks (shown after upload) -->
      <div id="pre-validation" class="hidden mb-4">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 border rounded-lg p-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <div class="font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Quick check</div>
          <div id="pv-frontmatter" class="flex items-center gap-2"></div>
          <div id="pv-words" class="flex items-center gap-2"></div>
          <div id="pv-claims" class="flex items-center gap-2"></div>
          <div id="pv-template" class="flex items-center gap-2"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Toggle to show/edit raw content -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
        <button type="button" onclick="toggleTextarea()" id="toggle-btn" class="text-xs text-gray-500 hover:text-otp-500 flex items-center gap-1">
          <svg id="toggle-icon" class="w-3 h-3 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/>
          </svg>
          <span id="toggle-label">Show raw content (paste or edit)</span>
        </button>
      </div>

      <div id="textarea-wrapper" class="hidden">
        <textarea id="oos-content" name="rawContent" rows="30"
          class="w-full font-mono text-sm border rounded-lg p-4 focus:border-otp-500 focus:ring-1 focus:ring-otp-500"
          placeholder="Or paste your OOS markdown here. Include YAML frontmatter between --- delimiters, then your sections and claims.

Example claim format:

**[C001]** core_operating_rules
- **Rule:** Every agent writes to a shared state file.
- **Why:** Direct access creates race conditions.
- **Failure mode:** Agents get conflicting data.
- **Confidence:** HIGH
- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT
- **Scope:** All agents."></textarea>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-between mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400">
        <span id="word-count">0 words (need 1800-3000)</span>
        <span id="claim-count">0 claims detected</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 4: Validate & Publish -->
    <div class="flex gap-3">
      <button type="button" onclick="validateAndFix()" id="validate-btn" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-100 border rounded-lg font-medium text-sm hover:bg-gray-200">
        Validate & Auto-Fix
      </button>
      <button type="button" onclick="publishOOS()" id="publish-btn" class="px-6 py-3 bg-otp-500 text-white rounded-lg font-medium text-sm hover:bg-otp-400">
        Validate & Publish
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- Validation Results -->
    <div id="validation-results" class="mt-6 hidden">

      <!-- Auto-fixes applied -->
      <div id="fix-results" class="hidden mb-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2" id="fix-header"></h3>
        <div id="fix-list" class="space-y-1"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Unfixable issues -->
      <div id="unfixable-results" class="hidden mb-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-orange-600 mb-2" id="unfixable-header"></h3>
        <div id="unfixable-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>

      <div id="validation-errors" class="hidden">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-2">Remaining errors (must fix before publishing)</h3>
        <div id="error-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-warnings" class="hidden mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-yellow-600 mb-2">Warnings (recommended to fix)</h3>
        <div id="warning-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="pii-flags" class="hidden mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-2">PII Detected (must resolve)</h3>
        <div id="pii-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="all-clear" class="hidden mt-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-green-800 text-sm">
          All checks passed. Ready to publish.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-success" class="hidden mt-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-green-800">
          OOS published successfully! <a id="published-link" href="#" class="underline">View your published OOS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>

<script>
const textarea = document.getElementById('oos-content');
const uploadZone = document.getElementById('upload-zone');
const fileInput = document.getElementById('file-input');
let textareaVisible = false;

// ---- File Upload ----

function handleFile(file) {
  if (!file) return;

  const validExts = ['.md', '.markdown', '.txt'];
  const ext = '.' + file.name.split('.').pop().toLowerCase();
  if (!validExts.includes(ext)) {
    alert('Please upload a .md, .markdown, or .txt file.');
    return;
  }

  // 500KB limit
  if (file.size > 512000) {
    alert('File too large. Maximum size is 500KB.');
    return;
  }

  const reader = new FileReader();
  reader.onload = function(e) {
    const content = e.target.result;

    // Normalize line endings (Windows CRLF -> LF)
    const normalized = content.replace(/\r\n/g, '\n').replace(/\r/g, '\n');

    // Fix smart quotes -> straight quotes
    const cleaned = normalized
      .replace(/[\u2018\u2019]/g, "'")
      .replace(/[\u201C\u201D]/g, '"');

    textarea.value = cleaned;
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));

    // Show success state
    document.getElementById('upload-prompt').classList.add('hidden');
    document.getElementById('upload-success').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('upload-filename').textContent = file.name;

    const sizeKB = (file.size / 1024).toFixed(1);
    document.getElementById('upload-meta').textContent = sizeKB + ' KB uploaded';

    uploadZone.classList.remove('border-gray-300', 'hover:border-otp-400');
    uploadZone.classList.add('border-green-300', 'bg-green-50/30');

    runPreValidation(cleaned);
  };
  reader.onerror = function() {
    alert('Failed to read file. Please try again.');
  };
  reader.readAsText(file);
}

fileInput.addEventListener('change', function(e) {
  handleFile(e.target.files[0]);
});

// Drag and drop
uploadZone.addEventListener('dragover', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  e.stopPropagation();
  uploadZone.classList.add('border-otp-500', 'bg-otp-50');
});

uploadZone.addEventListener('dragleave', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  e.stopPropagation();
  uploadZone.classList.remove('border-otp-500', 'bg-otp-50');
});

uploadZone.addEventListener('drop', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  e.stopPropagation();
  uploadZone.classList.remove('border-otp-500', 'bg-otp-50');
  if (e.dataTransfer.files.length > 0) {
    handleFile(e.dataTransfer.files[0]);
  }
});

function clearUpload(e) {
  e.stopPropagation();
  textarea.value = '';
  textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
  fileInput.value = '';

  document.getElementById('upload-prompt').classList.remove('hidden');
  document.getElementById('upload-success').classList.add('hidden');
  document.getElementById('pre-validation').classList.add('hidden');

  uploadZone.classList.remove('border-green-300', 'bg-green-50/30');
  uploadZone.classList.add('border-gray-300', 'hover:border-otp-400');
}

// ---- Pre-validation ----

function pvIcon(pass) {
  if (pass) return '<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>';
  return '<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-500 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>';
}

function runPreValidation(text) {
  const pv = document.getElementById('pre-validation');
  pv.classList.remove('hidden');

  // Frontmatter
  const hasFM = /^---\n[\s\S]*?\n---/.test(text);
  document.getElementById('pv-frontmatter').innerHTML =
    pvIcon(hasFM) + '<span class="' + (hasFM ? 'text-green-700' : 'text-red-600') + '">YAML frontmatter ' + (hasFM ? 'detected' : 'missing -- file must start with ---') + '</span>';

  // Word count
  const contentMatch = text.match(/^---[\s\S]*?---\n([\s\S]*)$/);
  const content = contentMatch ? contentMatch[1] : text;
  const words = content.trim().split(/\s+/).filter(function(w) { return w.length > 0; }).length;
  const wordsOk = words >= 1800 && words <= 3000;
  document.getElementById('pv-words').innerHTML =
    pvIcon(wordsOk) + '<span class="' + (wordsOk ? 'text-green-700' : 'text-red-600') + '">' + words + ' words ' + (words < 1800 ? '(need ' + (1800 - words) + ' more)' : words > 3000 ? '(over by ' + (words - 3000) + ')' : '(good)') + '</span>';

  // Claims
  const claimMatches = text.match(/\*\*\[C\d+\]\*\*/g);
  const claimCount = claimMatches ? claimMatches.length : 0;
  const claimsOk = claimCount >= 10;
  document.getElementById('pv-claims').innerHTML =
    pvIcon(claimsOk) + '<span class="' + (claimsOk ? 'text-green-700' : 'text-red-600') + '">' + claimCount + ' claims ' + (claimsOk ? '(good)' : '(need at least 10)') + '</span>';

  // Template detection from frontmatter
  var templateMatch = text.match(/template:\s*["']?(\w+)["']?/);
  var detectedTemplate = templateMatch ? templateMatch[1] : null;
  var templateOk = !!detectedTemplate;
  document.getElementById('pv-template').innerHTML =
    pvIcon(templateOk) + '<span class="' + (templateOk ? 'text-green-700' : 'text-red-600') + '">Template: ' + (detectedTemplate || 'not found in frontmatter') + '</span>';

  // Auto-select template radio if detected
  if (detectedTemplate) {
    var radio = document.querySelector('input[name="template"][value="' + detectedTemplate + '"]');
    if (radio) radio.checked = true;
  }
}

// ---- Textarea toggle ----

function toggleTextarea() {
  textareaVisible = !textareaVisible;
  document.getElementById('textarea-wrapper').classList.toggle('hidden', !textareaVisible);
  document.getElementById('toggle-icon').style.transform = textareaVisible ? 'rotate(90deg)' : '';
  document.getElementById('toggle-label').textContent = textareaVisible ? 'Hide raw content' : 'Show raw content (paste or edit)';
}

// ---- Word/claim count on textarea input ----

textarea.addEventListener('input', function() {
  var text = textarea.value;

  // Word count (rough -- content after frontmatter)
  var contentMatch = text.match(/^---[\s\S]*?---\n([\s\S]*)$/);
  var content = contentMatch ? contentMatch[1] : text;
  var words = content.trim().split(/\s+/).filter(function(w) { return w.length > 0; }).length;
  document.getElementById('word-count').textContent =
    words + ' words ' + (words < 1800 ? '(need ' + (1800 - words) + ' more)' : words > 3000 ? '(over by ' + (words - 3000) + ')' : '(good)');

  // Claim count
  var claimMatches = text.match(/\*\*\[C\d+\]\*\*/g);
  var claimCount = claimMatches ? claimMatches.length : 0;
  document.getElementById('claim-count').textContent =
    claimCount + ' claims detected ' + (claimCount < 10 ? '(need at least 10)' : '(good)');
});

function handleAuthError(data, status) {
  if (status === 401) {
    if (window.__clerk) {
      window.__clerk.openSignIn({ redirectUrl: '/publish' });
    } else {
      alert('Please sign in to publish.');
    }
    return true;
  }
  if (data.error?.code === 'ORG_NOT_FOUND') {
    window.location.href = '/dashboard';
    return true;
  }
  return false;
}

// ---- Validate & Auto-Fix ----

async function validateAndFix() {
  var btn = document.getElementById('validate-btn');
  btn.textContent = 'Fixing...';
  btn.disabled = true;

  var template = document.querySelector('input[name="template"]:checked').value;
  var rawContent = textarea.value;

  if (!rawContent.trim()) {
    alert('No content to validate. Upload a file or paste your OOS.');
    btn.textContent = 'Validate & Auto-Fix';
    btn.disabled = false;
    return;
  }

  try {
    var resp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos/fix', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ rawContent: rawContent, template: template }),
    });
    var data = await resp.json();

    // Replace content with fixed version
    if (data.fixed && data.fixCount > 0) {
      textarea.value = data.fixed;
      textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
    }

    showFixResults(data);

    // Update pre-validation if visible
    if (data.fixed) {
      runPreValidation(data.fixed);
    }

  } catch (e) {
    alert('Failed to validate. Check your content format.');
  } finally {
    btn.textContent = 'Validate & Auto-Fix';
    btn.disabled = false;
  }
}

async function publishOOS() {
  var btn = document.getElementById('publish-btn');
  btn.textContent = 'Publishing...';
  btn.disabled = true;

  var template = document.querySelector('input[name="template"]:checked').value;
  var rawContent = textarea.value;

  try {
    // Step 1: Auto-fix first
    var fixResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos/fix', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ rawContent: rawContent, template: template }),
    });
    var fixData = await fixResp.json();

    // Use fixed content
    var contentToPublish = fixData.fixed || rawContent;
    if (fixData.fixCount > 0) {
      textarea.value = contentToPublish;
      textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
    }

    // Check if there are unfixable errors that block publishing
    if (fixData.validation && !fixData.validation.valid) {
      showFixResults(fixData);
      btn.textContent = 'Validate & Publish';
      btn.disabled = false;
      return;
    }

    // Step 2: Create draft with fixed content
    var createResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ template: template, rawContent: contentToPublish }),
    });
    var createData = await createResp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(createData, createResp.status)) { btn.textContent = 'Validate & Publish'; btn.disabled = false; return; }

    if (createData.validation && !createData.validation.valid) {
      showFixResults(fixData);
      showValidation(createData);
      btn.textContent = 'Validate & Publish';
      btn.disabled = false;
      return;
    }

    // Step 3: Publish
    var publishResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos/' + createData.oosFile.id + '/publish', {
      method: 'POST',
    });
    var publishData = await publishResp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(publishData, publishResp.status)) { btn.textContent = 'Validate & Publish'; btn.disabled = false; return; }

    if (publishData.error) {
      showFixResults(fixData);
      showValidation(publishData);
      btn.textContent = 'Validate & Publish';
      btn.disabled = false;
      return;
    }

    // Show fixes applied, then success
    showFixResults(fixData);
    document.getElementById('validation-results').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('validation-success').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('published-link').href = '/oos/' + createData.oosFile.id;

  } catch (e) {
    alert('Failed to publish. Check your content and try again.');
  } finally {
    btn.textContent = 'Validate & Publish';
    btn.disabled = false;
  }
}

// ---- Display results ----

function showFixResults(data) {
  var container = document.getElementById('validation-results');
  container.classList.remove('hidden');

  // Reset all sections
  var sections = ['fix-results', 'unfixable-results', 'validation-errors', 'validation-warnings', 'pii-flags', 'all-clear', 'validation-success'];
  sections.forEach(function(id) { document.getElementById(id).classList.add('hidden'); });

  // Show fixes applied
  if (data.fixes && data.fixes.length > 0) {
    var fixDiv = document.getElementById('fix-results');
    fixDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('fix-header').textContent = data.fixes.length + ' issue' + (data.fixes.length === 1 ? '' : 's') + ' auto-fixed';
    document.getElementById('fix-list').innerHTML = data.fixes.map(function(f) {
      return '<div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-2 rounded text-xs text-green-800 flex items-start gap-2">'
        + '<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>'
        + '<div><span class="font-medium">' + f.description + '</span>'
        + (f.before !== f.after ? '<span class="text-green-600 ml-1">(' + f.before + ' &rarr; ' + f.after + ')</span>' : '')
        + '</div></div>';
    }).join('');
  }

  // Show unfixable issues
  if (data.unfixable && data.unfixable.length > 0) {
    var unfixDiv = document.getElementById('unfixable-results');
    unfixDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('unfixable-header').textContent = data.unfixable.length + ' issue' + (data.unfixable.length === 1 ? '' : 's') + ' require manual fix';
    document.getElementById('unfixable-list').innerHTML = data.unfixable.map(function(u) {
      return '<div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-orange-800">'
        + '<strong>' + u.field + ':</strong> ' + u.message
        + '</div>';
    }).join('');
  }

  // Show validation errors
  showValidation(data);

  // If everything is clean, show all-clear
  var hasErrors = data.validation && data.validation.errors && data.validation.errors.length > 0;
  var hasUnfixable = data.unfixable && data.unfixable.length > 0;
  if (!hasErrors && !hasUnfixable) {
    document.getElementById('all-clear').classList.remove('hidden');
  }
}

function showValidation(data) {
  var errorDiv = document.getElementById('validation-errors');
  var warningDiv = document.getElementById('validation-warnings');
  var piiDiv = document.getElementById('pii-flags');

  if (data.error?.details || (data.validation?.errors && data.validation.errors.length > 0)) {
    errorDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    var errors = data.error?.details || data.validation?.errors || [];
    document.getElementById('error-list').innerHTML = errors.map(function(e) {
      return '<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-red-800">' + (e.message || e.issue || JSON.stringify(e)) + '</div>';
    }).join('');
  }

  if (data.validation?.warnings && data.validation.warnings.length > 0) {
    warningDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('warning-list').innerHTML = data.validation.warnings.map(function(w) {
      return '<div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-yellow-800">' + w.message + '</div>';
    }).join('');
  }

  if (data.piiFlags && data.piiFlags.length > 0) {
    piiDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('pii-list').innerHTML = data.piiFlags.map(function(f) {
      return '<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-red-800">'
        + '<strong>' + f.type + ':</strong> "' + f.text + '" found in ' + f.location + '. <em>' + f.suggestion + '</em>'
        + '</div>';
    }).join('');
  }
}

